y expert and the book, after all, was an introductory text. Consequently, I read it critically, as a take on the dubious phenomenon. What distinguished it from such earlier works as Hans Jonas', other than her access to more recently available holographs, was its sociological orientation and emphasis on the role of women, both important additions to the tendencies of earlier scholarship.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/974210?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"religion","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/974210?shelf=religion"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/43364880"},"likeCount":16,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":1,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:106293767":{"id":106293767,"__typename":"User","legacyId":106293767,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1576529794i/106293767._UY200_CR33,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":145,"viewableName":"Bill","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/106293767-bill","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":26},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.kQvtnx-4HnUf6vJvxYS7GA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.kQvtnx-4HnUf6vJvxYS7GA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.dQcOD7xBzrtR7Wv4a8zv6g"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:106293767"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1594513154474,"createdAt":1594270557650,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1594295952095,"text":"Published in 1979, this award-winning book is still an excellent introduction to the Nag Hammadi library, discovered in Egypt in 1945, consisting of 52 Coptic texts bound in 13 codices. Nearly all of the works are of gnostic origin, and represent the most complete record of this sect that flourished during the earliest centuries of the Christian era.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003ePagels focuses on how these gnostic texts present strikingly different constructs of God, Jesus, and the church from those of the institutional Christian church that developed the orthodoxy that prevailed, to some extent, she suggests, because of political decisions favoring survival, including declaring gnostic beliefs to be heretical.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eChapters review a series of major conflicts between orthodox and gnostic beliefs, including whether Christ's resurrection was literal or symbolic, political dimensions of monotheism, the gender of God, martyrdom, the \"True\" church, and orthodox tradition vs. self-knowledge.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThis is a worthwhile read for anyone interested in the variety of beliefs competing within early Christianity.","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/106293767?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"national-book-award","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/106293767?shelf=national-book-award"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"nbcc-award","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/106293767?shelf=nbcc-award"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3343088355"},"likeCount":14,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":2,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:619520":{"id":619520,"__typename":"User","legacyId":619520,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1380779850i/619520._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":60,"viewableName":"Fredstrong","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/619520-fredstrong","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"follo