in any way, it had to be necessary as a bridge to the divine. Pagles shows how the establishment of what became Catholicism was politically, rather than divinely, inspired. A must read for anyone interested in early Christianity.\u003cbr /\u003e ","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/619520?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10076418"},"likeCount":13,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":2,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:2492588":{"id":2492588,"__typename":"User","legacyId":2492588,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406279836i/2492588._UY200_CR50,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":433,"viewableName":"Katie","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/2492588-katie","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":237},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.rs75Mp2Y6nmS589jDU1KQw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.rs75Mp2Y6nmS589jDU1KQw","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.dQcOD7xBzrtR7Wv4a8zv6g"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:2492588"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1629141012141,"createdAt":1315162154000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1315162544000,"text":"This is a really fascinating book, and a great introduction to Gnosticism. It's learned, it places theological ideas in a socio-political context, and it's enjoyable to read. Pagel's biggest success is in the way she ties the controversy between gnostic and orthodox ideas into contemporary social and political issues and uses them to explain why orthodox ideas ultimately won out. It paints a picture where orthodox Christianity isn't the camp that won because it's ideas were any 'truer,' but because it's ideas were far more widely accessible to the social and political structures that predominated in the 1st through 4th centuries.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eMy only criticism would be that Pagels occasionally over-emphasizes the dichotomy between orthodoxy and gnosticism and skims over any potential overlap. While she does acknowledge that the overlap is there, she doesn't really delve into the issue. At one point she points out that while gnostics tended to be internalized and personal, they also made extensive use of familial and social language in their writings. But she never expands upon it, which is a bit frustrating. But this is designed to be an introductory book, so that's certainly not a large flaw. Definitely worth a read if you're interested in the development of early Christiainty. ","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"medieval","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=medieval"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"theology","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=theology"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"intellectual-history","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=intellectual-history"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"religious-history","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=religious-history"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"early-christianity","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=early-christianity"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"history","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2492588?shelf=history"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/205165152"},"likeCount":12,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resour